In this memorandum, President Donald Trump delegates the authority to the Secretary of Energy, in coordination with the Secretary of Defense, the Attorney General, the Secretary of Homeland Security, and the Director of National Intelligence, to provide a briefing to Congress as required by section 3132(d) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019. The delegation mentioned in the memorandum will also apply to any future public law that is similar to the provision referenced. The Secretary of Energy is instructed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.